						<summary>

						<p>On the north wall, central shrine, Āpatsahāyēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Year 13: 984 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>Much damaged. It records the reclamation of land (probably owned by the temple) by Pūdi Kūttan of Puḷḷamaṅgalam in Nālūr-nāḍu in Tiruppaḻanam and endowment of the same for some service in the temples of Tiruppaḻaṉam, Tiruvaiyyāṟu, Tirunayttanam, Tiruvēdikuḍi and Āṟṟukuṉṟam. Reference is also made to the king, Parakēsarivarman when he was at Paḻaiyāṟai, but the context is not known.</p>						

						<p>Published in <hi rend="italic">S.I.I.,</hi> Vol. XIX No. 329. </p>						

						</summary>
